{"id": "EUVD-2025-15389", "enisaUuid": "aa9f9c49-4212-32de-afb5-90a2aed23b26", "description": "Undici is an HTTP/1.1 client for Node.js. Prior to versions 5.29.0, 6.21.2, and 7.5.0, applications that use undici to implement a webhook-like system are vulnerable. If the attacker set up a server with an invalid certificate, and they can force the application to call the webhook repeatedly, then they can cause a memory leak. This has been patched in versions 5.29.0, 6.21.2, and 7.5.0. As a workaound, avoid calling a webhook repeatedly if the webhook fails.", "datePublished": "2025-05-15T17:16:02", "dateUpdated": "2025-05-16T13:44:28", "baseScore": 3.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:L", "references": ["https://github.com/nodejs/undici/security/advisories/GHSA-cxrh-j4jr-qwg3", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-47279", "https://github.com/nodejs/undici/issues/3895", "https://github.com/nodejs/undici/pull/4088", "https://github.com/nodejs/undici"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-47279", "GHSA-cxrh-j4jr-qwg3"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "036689bc-823a-3570-887e-4dd46b9db85a", "product": {"name": "undici"}, "product_version": "6.0.0, < 6.21.2"}, {"id": "da16f1c2-a76d-3205-9015-57241501ca18", "product": {"name": "undici"}, "product_version": "< 5.29.0"}, {"id": "eb08a75d-7a85-33c1-8f0f-4362ecdd3546", "product": {"name": "undici"}, "product_version": "7.0.0, < 7.5.0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "eb10faee-444c-31f5-8180-0976b59f799a", "vendor": {"name": "nodejs"}}], "isExploited": false}